Communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The isolation of _E coli_ from the stools of some of the patients is not unexpected, as the organism is normal flora in the colon. Some _E. coli_ belong to enteric pathotypes such as enteropathogenic, enterotoxigenic, enteroinvasive, and enterohemorrhagic, which require specific testing to identify them. Therefore, the etiology or etiologies of this large and persistent outbreak is unclear. ProMED would like additional microbiologic information.

Barishal Division (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barisal_Division) is one of the 8 administrative divisions of Bangladesh. Located in the south-central part of the country, it has an area of 13 644.85 km2 (5268.31 sq mi) and a population of 8 325 666 at the 2011 census. It is bounded by Dhaka Division on the north, the Bay of Bengal on the south, Chattogram Division on the east, and Khulna Division on the west. The administrative capital, Barisal city, lies in the Padma River delta on an offshoot of the Arial Khan River. Barisal division is crisscrossed by numerous rivers that earned it the nickname "Dhan-Nodi-Khal, Ei tine Borishal" (rice, river, and canal built Barisal). A map showing the location can be found at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barisal_Division. - Mod.LL

